<h1>Introduction to JavaScript</h1>
<hr />
<p>JavaScript is a high-level, dynamic and interpreted programming language that is widely used for client-side web development to create dynamic and interactive user interfaces. It can also be used for server-side programming with technologies like Node.js.</p>
<hr />
<h1 class="font32 cap">Why is JavaScript Important?</h1>
<p>JavaScript is an essential part of web development as it enables developers to add interactivity and dynamic behavior to websites. With JavaScript, you can manipulate HTML and CSS, and make asynchronous requests to a server, updating parts of a web page without requiring a full refresh. This language is versatile and flexible, allowing for handling complex logic and data structures.</p>
<hr class="mr15" />
<h1 class="font32 cap">What Can JavaScript Do?</h1>
<p>JavaScript has a wide range of capabilities including:</p>
<ul>
  <li>DOM manipulation</li>
  <li>Asynchronous communication</li>
  <li>Form validation</li>
  <li>Animations and effects</li>
  <li>Single-page application development</li>
  <li>Server-side programming with Node.js</li>
  <li>and much more!</li>
</ul>
<p>With its versatility and ease of use, JavaScript has become one of the most widely-used programming languages in the world.</p>
